The paper focuses on using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to detect starting motions of cyclists in image sequences, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also utilizes a boosted stacking ensemble approach, which involves machine learning techniques such as extreme gradient boosting, and decision-level cooperation, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of sensors and smart devices, which relates to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the evaluation of the approach on real-world data, which falls under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
